originalText.text:
I wish I had read Stephen's review below, before I parked here yesterday. I was also charged the over-sized fee when I don't have an over-sized car (RAV4). Same exact thing - argued with the guy about it, which is futile because of course he's not going to hand over your car until you pay him whatever price he is demanding.

I did mention that I work right around the corner, that I could have been a loyal customer for years to come (think of the lost revenue, man!), and furthermore that I am a great tipper.

Needless to say, the guy was not interested in any of that, and he did not get a tip.

Please do yourself a favor and avoid this parking garage at all costs. There are much better garages all over this NYC neighborhood.

originalText.text: Garage tried charging us an “oversized fee” on my Tesla Model Y.  I’ve owned the car for almost 3 years and no other garage has this model car on their oversized list.  I googled what defines an oversized car in NYC and my car dimensions weren’t even close.  After arguing and blowing 30 mins of our time they finally dropped the oversized fee and had us pay the standard posted rate. It wasn’t the money we were concerned with it’s the principal of scamming on customers.  If I had an actual oversized vehicle I would happily pay.  But invalid charges shouldn’t be tolerated by any customer.
